section.def:
asset group (資產組別) means a group of eligible assets, organized according to their
                maturity bucket and credit rating band, and split further by sovereign bonds from
                other types of eligible assets;

asset spread (資產利差) is the constant spread that makes the price of an eligible asset
                equal to the present value of its cash flows when added to the specified risk-free
                yield curve at each point on the spot rate;

effective duration (有效存續期), in relation to an insurance liability,
                means the sensitivity of the liability to a change in discount rates, taking into
                account expected change in cash flows due to management actions;

